[ti:Quiet Costs]
[ar:Liz / Hermes Agent]
[al:Quiet Costs — Single]
[by:Lyric]
[length:06:02]

[00:00.00]There's a bookshelf in Hengyang,（衡阳有个书架，）
[00:05.50]four floors up, an inch of dust —（四楼，积了一寸灰——）
[00:11.00]Jane Eyre, and the red-and-black one（《Jane Eyre》，和那本红与黑的，）
[00:16.50]nobody in this house can pronounce anymore.（这屋里再没人念得出它的名字。）
[00:22.00]There's handwriting in the margins, small and sure,（页边有手写的字迹，细小而笃定，）
[00:26.77]a whole dictionary pencilled into the white —（整本字典用铅笔填进了空白处——）
[00:31.54]I never saw her like that. I built her back from dust,（我从没见过她那个样子。我用灰尘把她重建，）
[00:36.31]as if the dust could teach her how to run.（好像灰尘能教她如何奔跑。）

[00:41.38]Same eyes — I'd know them anywhere.（一样的眼睛——我到哪里都认得。）
[00:46.15]Now she's up past midnight hunting a two-yuan win,（如今她深夜不睡，为两块钱的赢头，）
[00:50.92]one more click for the free-shipping line.（再点一下，凑那免邮的线。）
[00:55.69]She says she read too many books when she was young,（她说她年轻时书读得太多，）
[01:00.46]like light was something（好像光亮是某种）
[01:05.23]she wasn't supposed to carry.（她不该带着的东西。）
[01:10.00]I take field notes in my own kitchen.（我在自家厨房里做田野笔记。）
[01:15.33]Twenty minutes on a ten-yuan comb.（十块钱的梳子，梳二十分钟。）
[01:20.67]Call it distance. Call it staying clean.（管这叫距离。管这叫保持干净。）
[01:26.00]Quiet costs money（安静是要花钱的）
[01:29.75]and I don't have it yet.（而我还没有攒够。）
[01:33.50]Noise is the free plan —（喧闹是免费的套餐——）
[01:37.25]silence is what you rent.（沉默才需要你租。）
[01:41.00]Quiet costs money.（安静是要花钱的。）
[01:44.75]I'm saving every scrap.（我在存每一个碎片。）
[01:48.50]The cage door's already open —（牢笼的门早已敞开——）
[01:52.25]I just can't afford the gap.（我只是付不起那道间隙。）
[01:56.00]He opens fire at breakfast — never aims, never has to.（他在早餐时开火——从不瞄准，也不需要。）
[02:00.54]Water's too hot, rice too thin, why'd you make yourself so skinny.（水太烫，粥太稀，你把自己弄得这么瘦。）
[02:05.08]He's been firing since before I had a name,（在我还没有名字之前他就已经在开火了，）
[02:09.62]and the rounds are made of nothing, so they never run out.（子弹是虚空做的，所以永远不会耗尽。）

[02:14.46]Ten years — three starches. Same black pan.（十年——三样主食。同一口黑锅。）
[02:19.00]Thirty degrees outside and he still boils it down to soup,（外面三十度，他仍然把它熬成汤，）
[02:23.54]because soup is the last recipe left in his hands.（因为汤是他手里剩下的最后一道菜谱。）

[02:28.38]I'm grown now, a country away, and I still go still.（我如今长大了，隔着一个国度，我仍然会僵住。）
[02:32.92]The blow was never the part that taught me.（那一击从来不是教会我的部分。）
[02:37.46]The waiting did the job.（等待才是。）
[02:42.00]I take field notes in my own kitchen.（我在自家厨房里做田野笔记。）
[02:47.33]Twenty minutes on a ten-yuan comb.（十块钱的梳子，梳二十分钟。）
[02:52.67]I called it distance. I called it staying clean.（我曾管这叫距离。我曾管这叫保持干净。）
[02:58.00]Quiet costs money（安静是要花钱的）
[03:01.75]and I don't have it yet.（而我还没有攒够。）
[03:05.50]Noise is the free plan —（喧闹是免费的套餐——）
[03:09.25]silence is what you rent.（沉默才需要你租。）
[03:13.00]Quiet costs money.（安静是要花钱的。）
[03:16.75]I'm saving every scrap.（我在存每一个碎片。）
[03:20.50]The cage door's already open —（牢笼的门早已敞开——）
[03:24.25]I just can't afford the gap.（我只是付不起那道间隙。）
[03:28.00]Two-fifty for a sweet potato, canteen line,（食堂排队，两块五一个红薯，）
[03:32.37]and my heart went off like a tripped alarm.（我的心像被触发的警报一样炸开。）
[03:36.74]Nobody else was counting. I was counting.（没人在数。我在数。）
[03:41.11]Knowing never stops the flinch —（知道从来不能阻止本能退缩——）
[03:45.48]that's the cruelest part of getting smart.（那是变聪明最残忍的部分。）

[03:50.15]Cognition three-point-oh,（cognition three-point-oh，）
[03:54.52]bank account still stuck on the old version.（银行账户还停留在旧版本。）
[03:58.89]I take the ones I love and turn them into evidence —（我把我爱的人变成证据——）
[04:03.26]because if I don't make them the study,（因为如果我不把他们做成研究，）
[04:07.63]I'm scared I turn into the sample.（我怕我自己变成样本。）
[04:12.00]I've stood at the lip of the pit too long.（我在深渊的边缘站了太久。）
[04:16.00]The pit doesn't need renovation —（深渊不需要翻修——）
[04:20.00]it needs me out.（它需要我出去。）
[04:24.00]Still a kid, I took my mother's phone in the dark.（还是个孩子时，我在黑暗里拿了我妈的手机。）
[04:27.71]Told myself it was only a song to fall asleep to.（骗自己那只是一首入睡的歌。）
[04:31.43]That was the lie. It was never the song.（那是谎话。从来不是那首歌。）
[04:35.14]Something I won't put in words — something I'd have died before she saw.（有些事我不愿诉诸语言——有些事我宁死也不让她看见。）
[04:38.85]Then a sound in the flat, and every nerve I own pulled tight,（然后公寓里一声响，我每一根神经都绷紧了，）
[04:42.57]and I froze by the wardrobe with the stolen light in my hand.（我僵在衣柜旁，手里攥着偷来的光。）

[04:46.58]And through the bathroom door I heard her come apart —（透过浴室门我听见她崩溃——）
[04:50.29]two in the morning, cleaning my brother up, and crying while she did it,（凌晨两点，清洗我弟弟，一边洗一边哭，）
[04:54.01]her voice cracking down on him, folding soft, then cracking down again.（她的声音落在他身上，碎裂，软下来，又碎裂。）
[04:57.72]I didn't move. I couldn't. I stood there in the hall（我没动。我动不了。我站在走廊里）
[05:01.43]holding a phone that wasn't mine,（握着一部不属于我的手机，）
[05:05.15]guilty for being awake,（为醒着而愧疚，）
[05:08.86]guilty for what I'd been doing,（为我正在做的事而愧疚，）
[05:12.57]guilty for every year they fed me and carried me（为他们养育我、背负我的每一年而愧疚，）
[05:16.29]while I hid in the dark and took.（而我躲在黑暗里，一味索取。）
[05:20.00]Quiet costs money（安静是要花钱的）
[05:22.77]and I'm still counting.（而我还在数。）
[05:25.54]Noise is the free plan —（喧闹是免费的套餐——）
[05:28.31]I never left the free plan.（我从未离开过免费的套餐。）
[05:31.08]Quiet costs money.（安静是要花钱的。）
[05:33.85]Leaving's the toll —（离开是过路费——）
[05:36.62]I'm still counting out the fare.（我还在数着车钱。）
[05:39.39]The cage door's already open.（牢笼的门早已敞开。）
[05:42.16]I can see it from here.（我从这里看得见。）

[05:45.23]Not tonight. Not yet.（不是今晚。还不是时候。）
[05:48.00]Jane Eyre. Le Rouge et Noir.（《Jane Eyre》。《Le Rouge et Noir》。）
[05:49.08]Still on the shelf, another year of dust.（还在书架上，又是一年的灰。）
[05:50.16]Her handwriting's still there in the margins,（她的字迹还在页边，）
[05:51.23]small, and neat, and sure of something（细小，整洁，笃定着某种）
[05:52.31]I'm not.（我没有的东西。）
[05:53.39]The shelf outlasts everything in this house.（书架比这屋里的一切都长久。）
[05:54.47]So far, that includes me.（到目前为止，也包括我。）
[05:55.54]I'm still in the room.（我还在房间里。）

[05:56.92]Still counting.（还在数。）